other_tests.findings: Continuous, generalized periodic discharges with occipital predominance at 1-2 Hz.

CSF analysis revealed colorless fluid, protein 38 mg/dL, glucose 62 mg/dL, 0 total nucleated cells and 8 erythrocytes, negative cultures, VZV IgM < 1.1, negative VZV PCR, negative paraneoplastic antibody panel, negative 14-3-3 protein, and negative cytology.
other_tests.changes_over_time: CSF sent to the National Prion Disease Surveillance Center subsequently returned with positive 14-3-3 protein, elevated t-tau protein 6301 pg/mL, and positive real-time quaking-induced conversion test (RTQuIC).
